.SS phabread
.sp
print patches from Phabricator suitable for importing:
.sp
.nf
.ft C
hg phabread DREVSPEC... [OPTIONS]
.ft P
.fi
.sp
DREVSPEC could be a Differential Revision identity, like \fBD123\fP, or just
the number \fB123\fP. It could also have common operators like \fB+\fP, \fB\-\fP,
\fB&\fP, \fB(\fP, \fB)\fP for complex queries. Prefix \fB:\fP could be used to
select a stack.  If multiple DREVSPEC values are given, the result is the
union of each individually evaluated value.  No attempt is currently made
to reorder the values to run from parent to child.
.sp
\fBabandoned\fP, \fBaccepted\fP, \fBclosed\fP, \fBneedsreview\fP, \fBneedsrevision\fP
could be used to filter patches by status. For performance reason, they
only represent a subset of non\-status selections and cannot be used alone.
.sp
For example, \fB:D6+8\-(2+D4)\fP selects a stack up to D6, plus D8 and exclude
D2 and D4. \fB:D9 & needsreview\fP selects "Needs Review" revisions in a
stack up to D9.
.sp
If \-\-stack is given, follow dependencies information and read all patches.
It is equivalent to the \fB:\fP operator.
.sp
